community student affairs haas center for public service students faculty alumni community about stanford university student affairs all stanford search submit community introduction the haas center strives to develop leaders who can help strengthen communities locally regionally or wherever there is a need our students are encouraged to connect their community service experiences to academic study in order to grow into effective civic leaders after graduation our alumni remain engaged in seeking solutions to the problems they have addressed as students whether as career specialists organizational leaders or volunteers we are grateful to all community members far and wide who have mentored and taught our students through haas center programs home for campus and community organizations connect with the haas center to involve stanford students in your work looking for students city manager in residence stanford public interest network spin for supporters support the haas center's work as a donor or a volunteer giving to the haas center volunteering at the haas center for colleges & universities learn about our programs and opportunities for partnership programs at a glance starting an early literacy program principles of ethical and effective service for parents explore how public service programs enhance a stanford education and open doors for local children pre k 12 parents stanford parents giving to the haas center connect with us facebook facebook twitter twitter video icon video stanford seal newsletter giving to haas action logo support our work haas center for public service 562 salvatierra walk stanford ca 94305 650 723 0992 hours m f 8 5 support our work feedback copyright 2011 stanford university terms of use copyright complaints report a problem with this site
